The paper deals with error correcting codes for a specific channel model, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The use of maximum distance separable (MDS) codes and maximum rank distance (MRD) Gabidulin block codes suggests a focus on coding theory (cs.CR) and algebraic coding theory (cs.DS). The consideration of streaming sources and packet erasure channels may also suggest a focus on networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI).
